lock.id\n  output?: string;\n  error?: string;\n}\n```\n\n**Why this structure:**\n- Reflects actual token flow: text and tool_calls are interleaved in model output\n- Tool results are blocks too, appearing after the call they respond to\n- Easy to reconstruct the full trace: just iterate `blocks` in order\n- For blame UI: filter to `tool_call` blocks where `name === \"edit_file\"` to find what changed\n\n**Example session:**\n\n```json\n{\n  \"id\": \"sess_abc123\",\n  \"turns\": [\n    {\n      \"type\": \"human\",\n      \"content\": \"Add error handling to the login function\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"type\": \"assistant\",\n      \"model\": \"claude-sonnet-4-20250514\",\n      \"blocks\": [\n        { \"type\": \"text\", \"text\": \"I'll add try/catch error handling.\" },\n        { \n          \"type\": \"tool_call\",\n          \"id\": \"tc_1\",\n          \"name\": \"edit_file\",\n          \"input\": { \"path\": \"src/auth/login.ts\", \"old_string\": \"...\", \"new_string\": \"...\" }\n        },\n        { \"type\": \"tool_result\", \"tool_call_id\": \"tc_1\", \"output\": \"File edited\" },\n        { \"type\": \"text\", \"text\": \"I've added error handling. The function now catches...\" }\n      ]\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n## 2. Storage Strategy\n\n**Two-tier approach:**\n\n```\nGit Notes (refs/notes/assert-traces)     Local Storage (.git/assert/)\n┌─────────────────────────────────┐     ┌──────────────────────────────┐\n│ {                               │     │ traces/                      │\n│   \"trace_id\": \"tr_xyz\",         │ ──► │   sess_abc123.json  (full)   │\n│   \"session_id\": \"sess_abc123\",  │     │   sess_def456.json  (full)   │\n│   \"files\": [...],               │     │                              │\n│   \"summary\": {                  │     │ index.json                   │\n│     \"prompt\": \"Add error...\",   │     │   (session_id -> file map)   │\n│     \"model\": \"claude-sonnet-4-20250514\"  │     │                              │\n