            "content": "---\nname: assert-capture\ndescription: View and manage captured agent traces for Assert Labs analysis\ndisable-model-invocation: true\n---\n\n# Assert Trace Capture\n\nView and manage agent traces captured by the Assert plugin.\n\n## Trigger\n\nUse this skill when you want to:\n- View recently captured agent traces\n- Check the status of trace capture\n- Export traces for analysis\n- Clear or manage stored traces\n\n## Workflow\n\n1. **Check capture status**\n   - Read the state file at `.cursor/hooks/state/assert-trace-capture.json`\n   - Report total traces captured and last capture time\n\n2. **List recent traces**\n   - List files in `.cursor/hooks/state/assert-traces/`\n   - Show summary of recent trace files (conversation ID, status, timestamp)\n\n3. **View specific trace**\n   - If user requests a specific trace, read and display its contents\n   - Summarize key information: conversation ID, status, loop count, transcript path\n\n4. **Export traces** (if requested)\n   - Combine traces into a single export file\n   - Output to user-specified location or default export directory\n\n## Output\n\n- Summary of trace capture status\n- List of recent traces with key metadata\n- Detailed trace information if requested\n\n## Configuration\n\nThe following environment variables control capture behavior:\n\n- `ASSERT_MAX_TRACES` - Maximum traces to keep in state (default: 100)\n- `ASSERT_CAPTURE_CONTENT` - Whether to capture full transcript content (default: true)\n- `ASSERT_CAPTURE_ALL` - Whether to capture aborted/error traces (default: false)\n- `ASSERT_DEDUPLICATE` - Whether to deduplicate by generation_id (default: true)\n\n## State Files\n\n- **State file**: `.cursor/hooks/state/assert-trace-capture.json`\n- **Trace files**: `.cursor/hooks/state/assert-traces/trace-{conversation_id}-{timestamp}.json`\n",
