          "input": {
            "content": "# Assert Trace Capture Plugin\n\nA Cursor plugin that captures agent traces and outputs for analysis and debugging via Assert Labs.\n\n## Features\n\n- **Automatic trace capture**: Hooks into agent completion events to capture traces\n- **Transcript preservation**: Optionally captures full transcript content\n- **Incremental state**: Maintains state across sessions with deduplication\n- **Configurable behavior**: Environment variables to control capture settings\n\n## Installation\n\n1. Copy the `cursor-plugin` directory to your workspace\n2. Ensure Bun is installed (`curl -fsSL https://bun.sh/install | bash`)\n3. The plugin will automatically activate when Cursor detects the `.cursor-plugin/plugin.json`\n\n## How It Works\n\n### Hook System\n\nThe plugin uses Cursor's hook system to capture agent traces:\n\n1. **Stop Hook** (`hooks/assert-stop.ts`): Fires after each agent completion\n   - Receives conversation metadata (ID, status, loop count)\n   - Captures transcript path and optionally full content\n   - Stores traces in `.cursor/hooks/state/assert-traces/`\n   - Maintains state in `.cursor/hooks/state/assert-trace-capture.json`\n\n### Captured Data\n\nEach trace includes:\n- `timestamp`: ISO timestamp of capture\n- `conversation_id`: Unique conversation identifier\n- `generation_id`: Unique generation identifier (for deduplication)\n- `status`: Completion status (completed, aborted, error)\n- `loop_count`: Number of agentic loops executed\n- `transcript_path`: Path to the transcript file\n- `transcript_content`: Full transcript content (if enabled)\n- `transcript_mtime`: Transcript file modification time\n\n## Configuration\n\nSet these environment variables to customize behavior:\n\n| Variable | Default | Description |\n|----------|---------|-------------|\n| `ASSERT_MAX_TRACES` | `100` | Maximum traces to keep in state |\n| `ASSERT_CAPTURE_CONTENT` | `true` | Whether to capture full transcript content |\n| `ASSERT_CAPTURE_ALL` | `false` | Whether to capture aborted/error traces |\n| `ASSERT_DEDUPLICATE` | `true` | Whether to deduplicate by generation_id |\n\n## Skills\n\n### assert-capture\n\nView and manage captured agent traces.\n\n```\nRun the assert-capture skill to view trace status and recent captures.\n```\n\n## Agents\n\n### trace-analyzer\n\nAnalyzes captured traces to identify patterns and insights.\n\n```\nInvoke the trace-analyzer agent to analyze captured traces.\n```\n\n## File Structure\n\n```\ncursor-plugin/\n├── .cursor-plugin/\n│   └── plugin.json          # Plugin manifest\n├── hooks/\n│   ├── hooks.json           # Hook configuration\n│   └── assert-stop.ts       # Stop hook implementation\n├── skills/\n│   └── assert-capture/\n│       └── SKILL.md         # Trace management skill\n├── agents/\n│   └── trace-analyzer.md    # Trace analysis agent\n├── assets/                  # Plugin assets\n├── README.md\n└── LICENSE\n```\n\n## State Files\n\nAll state is stored in `.cursor/hooks/state/`:\n\n- `assert-trace-capture.json` - Main state file with trace metadata\n- `assert-traces/` - Directory containing individual trace JSON files\n\n## Development\n\n### Prerequisites\n\n- [Bun](https://bun.sh/) runtime\n- Cursor IDE with plugin support\n\n### Testing\n\nRun the hook manually for testing:\n\n```bash\necho '{\"conversation_id\":\"test-123\",\"status\":\"completed\",\"loop_count\":5}' | bun run hooks/assert-stop.ts\n```\n\n## License\n\nMIT License - see LICENSE file for details.\n",
